extends templates/base

block content
  h2 Navs
  section
    h3 Navbar
    p
      | Define a navbar through the usual html markup, and simply add the #[+code("navbar")] class, along with an optional color modifier class
      | to define the color scheme for the navbar. Content can be aligned to the right by adding a second #[+code("<ul>")] inside the navbar and
      | giving it the #[+code("right")] class. A second right-aligned list can be added to the nav to center the first one.

    nav.navbar.primary
      ul
        li
          a(href="#") Item 1
        li
          a(href="#") Item 2
      ul.right
        li
          a(href="#") Item 3

  section
    h3 Links
    p
      | Mark a link as active by adding the #[+code('active')] class to it.

    nav.navbar.secondary
      .brand BigCorp
      ul
        li
          a(href="#") Link 1
          a.active(href="#") Link 2
          a(href="#") Link 3
          a(href="#") Link 4

  section
    h3 Navbar Items
    p
      | You can add buttons, logos, inline forms, or anything else to a navbar.

    nav.navbar.primary
      .brand Brand Name
      ul
        li
          a(href="#") Item Link
      .right
        .field-inline
          .attached
            input.input
            button.outlined Click Me
        button.success Log In

